ntal structures expressed with strong temporal and spatial regularity.\nUsing this framework, we explore the complex interplay between social and\ngeospatial behavior, documenting how the formation of cores are preceded by\ncoordination behavior in the communication networks, and demonstrating that\nsocial behavior can be predicted with high precision.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Jun 2015 19:04:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 30 Dec 2016 12:27:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-02"}
